.IX Xref "HAS_LROUNDL"
.IX Item "HAS_LROUNDL"
This symbol, if defined, indicates that the \f(CW\*(C`lroundl\*(C'\fR routine is
available to return the nearest integral value away from zero of
the long double argument value.
.ie n .IP """HAS_MODFL""" 4
.el .IP \f(CWHAS_MODFL\fR 4
