.SH "Reference-counted stack manipulation"
.IX Header "Reference-counted stack manipulation"
Functions for pushing and pulling items on the stack when the
stack is reference counted. They are intended as replacements
for the old PUSHs, POPi, EXTEND etc pp macros within pp
functions.
.ie n .IP """rpp_context""" 4
.el .IP \f(CWrpp_context\fR 4
.IX Xref "rpp_context"
.IX Item "rpp_context"
NOTE: \f(CW\*(C`rpp_context\*(C'\fR is \fBexperimental\fR and may change or be
removed without notice.
.Sp
Impose void, scalar or list context on the stack.
First, pop \f(CW\*(C`extra\*(C'\fR items off the stack, then when \f(CW\*(C`gimme\*(C'\fR is:
\&\f(CW\*(C`G_LIST\*(C'\fR:   return as-is.
\&\f(CW\*(C`G_VOID\*(C'\fR:   pop everything back to \f(CW\*(C`mark\*(C'\fR
\&\f(CW\*(C`G_SCALAR\*(C'\fR: move the top stack item (or \f(CW&PL_sv_undef\fR if none) to
\&\f(CW\*(C`mark+1\*(C'\fR and free everything above it.
.RS 4
.Sp
.Vb 1
\& void  rpp_context(SV **mark, U8 gimme, SSize_t extra)
